<br>
The draught line of nukes are often used for low agro, high dps damage with less risk of resist/wasted mana. With BoR and Quickening of Solusek, these cast in 2.0 seconds, with a recast of 2.25, and legs have a cast time of 2.0. Essentially wizards who go with draughts are often twisting every 2 seconds. That sounds like a more frantic pace of twisting if you ask me. <br>
<br>
A wizard trying to do the most dps possible is just like a bard who is trying to keep as many songs up as possible. You have to assert yourself into doing better.  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4366"><br>
